	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99884568445880><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Grouping as a shammy</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 26th 1:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, I have to say how disappointed I was with some of the topics on this site. Yesterday was my first time checking it out, and the first half of all the topics had NO SHAMAN related points whatsoever.But I did decide to check out the entire screen before making my final judgement, and to my delight, found several good discussions, particularly on soloing a shaman. Thanks for the advice. However, the vast majority of the time I tend to group, and I just wanted some general tips. A lot of our spells overlap with other classes, and the only thing I know of for sure is that our slow is the best :) How about the rest? As well, I am a 35 shaman now, and finding it increasingly difficult to keep up with a full group's heals, esp if the group is tank heavy. I find myself having to be a bit blunt at times, because it is those tank heavy groups who want full heals and full buffs, and that just can't happen all the time. So if anyone has any tips, I would appreciate it greatly. <br><br>Thanks, <br>Mikayla<br>35 Shamaness<br>Innoruuk<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
