	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99891561167095><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99891561167095>RE: Grouping as a shammy</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99891561167095#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 27th 8:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For the most part, in a tank heavy group buffs are not necessary.&nbsp;&nbsp;In such groups I just cast regen and speed on the tanks, and heal as needed.  Also cast regen on yourself and use canabalize.  Convert about 2/5 of your health to mana and then med and regen, you will regain mana much faster this way.  <br><br>Also never forget, if they get too bitchy, you can solo they can't.....<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
